The paper proposes a new algorithm for Maximum Inner Product Search (MIPS) that does not require preprocessing and allows users to control the suboptimality of the results. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
